  "returns": "mindspore.ops.logsumexpmindspore.ops.logsumexp(input,dim,keepdim=False)[source]Calculate the log of summed exponentials of the tensor along a specified dimension.\\[logsumexp(input) = \\log(\\sum(e^{input-input_{max}})) + input_{max}\\]Parametersinput(Tensor) – The input tensor.dim(Union[int,tuple(int),list(int)]) – Specify the dimension for computation. If(), compute all\nelements in theinput.keepdim(bool,optional) – Whether the output tensor has dim retained. DefaultFalse.ReturnsTensorSupported Platforms:AscendGPUCPUExamples>>>importmindspore>>>input=mindspore.tensor([[9.,3,4,5],...[5,2,7,4],...[8,1,3,6]])>>># case 1: By default, compute the log of summed exponential of all elements.>>>output=mindspore.ops.logsumexp(input,())>>>print(output)9.475807>>>>>># case 2: Compute the log of summed exponential along dim 0.>>>output=mindspore.ops.logsumexp(input,0)>>>print(output)[9.326562  3.4076054 7.065884  6.4076056]>>>>>># case 3: If keepdim=True, the output shape will be same of that of the input.>>>output=mindspore.ops.logsumexp(input,1,True)>>>print(output)[[9.02716 ][7.175515][8.133643]]",
